      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, maintained to exacting standards. This example features the legendary 13B-REW rotary engine with its sequential twin-turbocharger system functioning flawlessly, delivering a linear power band and crisp boost transition. The chassis remains structurally rigid, benefiting from a factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential that ensures optimal torque distribution. All vacuum lines have been refreshed with high-temp silicone to prevent common heat-soak issues, and the apex seals show excellent compression across all faces. Finished in its original pigment with zero oxidation, the vehicle retains its near-perfect weight distribution and lightweight aluminum components. This is a mechanically superior specimen for the discerning collector.",
